other_tests.findings: Atrial fibrillation with a rapid ventricular response and a heart rate of 123 beats per minute.
Diffuse slowing of the background at the theta range with superimposed theta and delta activity bilaterally without epileptiform discharges.
Negative cultures for Cytomegalovirus, West Nile virus, Herpes simplex viruses (HSV-1 and HSV-2), and John Cunningham virus. Human immunodeficiency virus and hepatitis panel were also negative.
Elevated coproporphyrin I (163 µg/L; normal range 0-15 µg/L) and coproporphyrin III (778 micrograms per liter; normal range 0-49 µg/L).
Elevated coproporphyrin III: coproporphyrin I (CIII: CI) ratio (2.94; normal range <1.20).
